text:
(1) Cooper Street, at the S.E. corner of Central Ave., showing an old hotel razed in October 1925. (This property was once in the Van Voorhies family). 1922.

folder: Cooper Street & Central Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
149-159 Cooper Street, at and north of Central Ave. The corner house (149), was at one time occupied by one Hatfield, who used it as a residence and also for the manufacture of "fire-works". It was later used as a saloon.

March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
